Add @water{300%ml}(cold, salted) to a #medium pot{} with a tight-fitting #lid{}.

Stir in the @rice{150%g} and bring to the boil.

Once boiling, lower the heat to medium and cover with the #lid{}.

Leave to cook for ~{10%minutes}, then remove the #pot{} from the heat (still covered) and leave to the side for another ~{10%minutes} or until ready to serve (the rice will continue to cook in its own steam).

While the rice cooks, halve the @bell pepper{1}(halved) and discard the core and seeds. Slice into thin strips.

Peel and grate the @garlic{1%clove}(peeled and grated) (or use a #garlic press{}).

Slice the @sugar snap peas{150%g} in half.

Place a #medium pan{} over high heat with a drizzle of @oil{to taste}.

Once the oil is hot, add the pepper.

Stir-fry until just soft, ~{3-4%minutes}.

Add the @Irish pork mince{250%g} to the pepper and cook until browned, ~{5-6%minutes}.

Use a #spoon{} to break it up as it cooks.

Season with @salt{to taste} and @pepper{to taste}.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw mince. Pork is cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

Once the pork is browned, add the garlic and sugar snaps to the pan and stir-fry for ~{1%minute}.

Stir in the @teriyaki sauce{2%sachets} and cook for ~{1%minute} more.

Taste and season with salt and pepper if needed.

Add a splash of @water{to taste} if it's a little dry.

Fluff up the rice with a #fork{}, then share between #bowls{}.

Top with the teriyaki pork stir-fry.